added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds another talent competition to find the second best superhero team in the world.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and the Titans must find a way to beat the Hive Five.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 1
added.description: In this episode of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans gain the ability to transform into cars.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 2
added.description: In the exciting conclusion of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans must learn to work together to stop Dr. Military.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter One
added.description: Cyborg becomes trapped in the alternate reality of Night Begins to Shine with a Dragon who wants to steal the song for his own evil purposes.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Two
added.description: Without Cyborg, Beast Boy feels lost and sets out to find himself, but ends up meeting a music legend.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Three
added.description: The Titans return to the alternate reality to save Cyborg but will they be able to defeat the Dragon?

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Four
added.description: In a final epic battle, the Titans and their musician friends square off against the Dragon for control of The Night Begins to Shine.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds a talent competition to find a superhero worthy of joining the team.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and Robin tries everything to win.

added.title: Missing
added.description: Killer Moth offers a reward for Silkie's return, but will Silkier be happier away from the Titans?

added.title: Uncle Jokes
added.description: BB and Cyborg invite Starfire to join in their fun as long as she avoids dreaded uncle jokes.

added.title: Grandma Voice
added.description: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Christmas Parties
added.description: The Bears have been invited to all their friends' Christmas parties. In an effort to have time to crash Nom Nom's huge star-studded bash, the Bears first try to make quick stops at all their friends' parties throughout the night.

added.title: The Perfect Tree
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear drive up north to find the perfect Christmas tree. Meanwhile, Grizz and Panda are in charge of decorating Chloe's house.

added.title: Professor Lampwick
added.description: Chloe's professor is too mean to give her any face time to talk over her poor grade. The Bears take things into their own hands to help, causing big trouble for Chloe.

added.title: Cousin Jon
added.description: When the Bears attend Chloe's family reunion, they fall victim to the mischievous pranks of Chloe's cousin, Jon.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: The Limit
added.description: The Watterson family faces Mom's wrath in a supermarket.

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Roots
added.description: When Mom sees Darwin gazing longingly at a fish-tank, she thinks their mammalian lifestyle isn't fulfilling her adopted son and deep down he longs to connect with his fishy roots. So the family try to reconnect him with his aquatic culture. They try fish-food, fish-language and even fish clothes. But when none of it works, they realize they may have to let him go.

added.title: The Fuss
added.description: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else!

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The Deal
added.description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: The Ad
added.description: To make ends meet, the Wattersons are forced to rent out their house. However, with nowhere else to stay they decide to secretly remain at the house. When they accidentally surprise their guests, an elderly pair of fainting goats, they faint...unsurprisingly.  The Wattersons fear the worst and attempt to cover up this "accident".

added.title: The Possession
added.description: Nicole has decided it's time to throw out the family's refrigerator. This doesn't go down too well with Richard, as it's his favorite possession. When it turns out the refrigerator is also a magical storage facility for childhood emotions and memories, it makes sense that Richard is having a hard time letting go.

added.title: The Master
added.description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?

added.title: Alien X-Tinction
added.description: When the Tennysons are attacked by a villainous, dimension-hopping Omni-alien known only as Alien X, they soon meet a parallel universe version of Max who opens the door to hosting multiple Bens and Gwens, forming an alien hero army to combat this threat.

added.title: Ben Gen 10
added.description: When Ben meets a young Generator Rex on the run from a hostile Providence, he must work through a series of misunderstandings, and defeat the dark wizard Hex in order to save the world from a malfunctioning Omnitrix infecting the world's human population with alien DNA.

added.title: Ben 10,010
added.description: In a future where an adult Gwen Tennyson is president and the world is being taken over by the alien horde known as the Xerge, a disillusioned Ben 10000 is called out of retirement to recruit his 10-year old version from the past - only together can the battle-worn adult and the impulsive child save a future under siege.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: Can I Keep It?
added.description: After stumbling upon a cute cat-dog-rabbit creature hybrid, or "Cadobbit," Ben ignores Grandpa Max's advice and sneaks the animal onto the Rustbucket, but is quickly in over his head as Dr. Amino's creation turns on him!

added.title: All Koiled Up
added.description: When Ben grows impatient with the snail like pace of gardening, he goes O-E Overflow to pick up the pace and accidentally floods the community garden, but once a giant sink hole appears and frees King Koil and his Kimodo Dragon from below, Ben must quickly right his wrong and capture the baddies if he is to save the coastal city of Bayburgh.

added.title: The Charm Offensive
added.description: After Ben gets too much publicity for his alien antics in Fort Knox, a jealous Gwen feels unappreciated and looks to ease her pain with ice cream, but once she is confronted by Charmcaster looking to avenge Michael Morningstar, Gwen must prove to herself she's a worthy member of Team Tennyson if they are to survive.

added.title: Ye Olde Laser Duel
added.description: As team Tennyson admires the efficiency of a super modern train station, Ben is quick to sniff out one of Steam Smythe's robots holding up the line. Once the fed up villain tricks our hero into accepting a duel, the fate of the Omnitrix hangs in the balance and it's up to Ben to set things right.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: Robo Teacher
added.description: When a substitute teacher fills in for Chef, Duncan thinks it's going to be the best day ever. He's wrong.

added.title: Glove Glove Me Do
added.description: Owen's newly found gloves make him great at everything. But this greatness comes at a high price.

added.title: The Tooth About Zombies
added.description: When Gwen's favorite event, the Zombie March, falls on the same day as Noah's nightmare event, dental hygienist check up day, Gwen and Noah find a way to help each other out.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple helps Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Go With the Flow
added.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: Level Thirteen
added.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

added.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
added.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 1
added.description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

added.title: #LeagueOfShadows Part 2
added.description: Under the control of Red Kryptonite, Kara Danvers is brainwashed by rock 'n' roll front man Ra's al Ghul and sent on a mission to purify the world... starting with the terrible music of Karen Beecher's favorite boy band!

added.title: #BreakingNews
added.description: Lois Lane's attempt to get an internship at the Daily Planet leads to her trying to unmask the Super Hero Girls, which forces the girls to a battle of wits with their greatest nemesis yet.

added.title: #CrashCourse
added.description: When a high-speed chase breaks out during her driver's test, Diana Prince's desire to fight evil clashes with her desire to undergo a World of Man teenage rite of passage, getting her license.

added.title: #HousePest
added.description: When the Super Hero Girls discover that Diana doesn't actually have a home, they gladly open theirs up to her… until they discover that life with an Amazon is much more challenging than they expected.

added.title: Exodus Part 1
added.description: Fleeing the destruction of their home planet Thundera, Lion-O and the ThunderCats land on the mysterious, dangerous, all-around awesome world of Third Earth! But their enemies, the Mutants of Plun-Darr have followed them and it turns out Third Earth already has a Mumm-Ra problem, can Lion-O learn the ropes of being a leader in time?

added.title: Exodus Part 2
added.description: Fleeing the destruction of their home planet Thundera, Lion-O and the ThunderCats land on the mysterious, dangerous, all-around awesome world of Third Earth! But their enemies, the Mutants of Plun-Darr have followed them and it turns out Third Earth already has a Mumm-Ra problem, can Lion-O learn the ropes of being a leader in time?

added.title: The Legend of Boggy Ben
added.description: Lion-O has gotten a hold of the last jar of Thundersnaps, the best cookies Thundera had to offer! But a difficult to open cookie jar is gonna send Lion-O and Cheetara chasing down a legend, a Boggy Ben-related legend.

added.title: Prank Call
added.description: Lion-O wants to prove to the ThunderKittens that he's not just some boring old adult, like Tygra, even if it means ignoring his instincts and messing with an obviously evil crystal.

added.title: Driller
added.description: Panthro is getting a little fed up with having to fix things around the Cats' Lair constantly, which is unfortunate because the ThunderCats are about to be attacked by an unstoppable drilling robot, and he's gonna break everything!

added.title: Fusion Cuisine
added.description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.

added.title: Alone Together
added.description: The Gems try to teach Steven to use his fusion powers.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Crack the Whip
added.description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Lion 3: Straight to Video
added.description: Lion won't stop laying on Steven's face while he sleeps.

added.title: Rose's Scabbard
added.description: Steven joins Pearl on a special mission to a place that belonged to Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: Legend of Torbaclaun
added.description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Flyaway
added.description: When Adorabat's spirit transcends her body during a meditation exercise, Mao Mao and Badgerclops have to figure out a way to return her to the real world.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: No Shortcuts
added.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Memory of a Memory
added.description: To save Marceline from a sleep spell, Finn and Jake must enter her mind and find the wake spell deep inside her memory.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Blenanas
added.description: Finn's latest literary work is met with only derision so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

added.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
added.description: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum.

added.title: Dream of Love
added.description: Tree Trunks is courted by an oinking suitor, but much to Jake's dismay, this interferes with her baking habits.

added.title: Beyond This Earthly Realm
added.description: When Finn finds a porcelain lamb, it transports him into the spirit world and only the Ice King can help get him out!

added.title: Card Wars
added.description: Finn and Jake embark on an epic game of Card Quest.

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess. Is Princess Bubblegum jealous?

added.title: Belly of the Beast
added.description: In order to cure the stomach ache of a giant, Finn and Jake must break up a party happening in his belly.

added.title: City of Thieves
added.description: Finn tries not to be corrupted by the City of Thieves.

added.title: Dungeon
added.description: Finn tries to conquer a dungeon without Jake's help.

added.title: Donny
added.description: In an attempt to save a village, Finn and Jake rehabilitate Donny the Ogre, who's a real jerk.

added.title: Tooth Trouble
added.description: Puppycorn loses his first tooth and Unikitty's excited for her little bro, now he​ ​gets a visit from​ ​the​ ​legendary Tooth Fairy!​ ​But when the Tooth Fairy is a no-show, Unikitty and her friends take on the mantle and responsibilities. But will they play too fast and loose with loose teeth and hit a raw nerve?

added.title: Camp Unikitty
added.description: The gang's set for an awesome weekend of glamorous, easy-living camping out in fun, friendly nature! But when Hawkodile challenges their idea of camping (it should be a fight for survival in the hostile woods), the gang switch places, with Hawkodile living a luxurious glamp life while Unikitty and the others survive in the wild. Will Unikitty still believe the "great outdoors" are all that great if they meet their doom by natural causes?

added.title: Perfect Moment
added.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

added.title: Hawkodile Sensei
added.description: On a routine mission, Hawkodile finds some defenseless chipmunks that imprint on him.​ ​The bird bodyguard takes it upon himself to become their Sensei teach the younglings his warrior ways, but Unikitty worries his training is too intense. Will Hawkodile's "all work, no play" lifestyle push the chipmunks too far?

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device
added.description: When boredom levels in the castle hit dangerously high levels, Dr. Fox conveniently introduces her P.L.O.T. Device. When pressed, this device alters reality to make it more exciting. Richard warns that this might be dangerous, but no one listens. It's not long till he is proven correct and life in the castle becomes dangerously exciting.

added.title: Who Took Toast
added.description: When Toast disappears from Unikitty's party she leads a search to find him and expose the toast-napper.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Primogenita
added.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Firstbourne
added.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

added.title: Hierro y piedra
added.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Iron & Stone
added.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.

added.title: Radio Ninjago libre
added.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
added.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

added.title: Como construir un dragon
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: How to Build a Dragon
added.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

added.title: El camino dorado
added.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Gilded Path
added.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

added.title: Birthday Gift
added.description: Rigby always gives Mordecai the worst birthday gifts, but this year it's going to be different.

added.title: Cat Videos
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get Benson to stop watching cat videos.

added.title: Struck by Lightning
added.description: Muscle Man and High Five Ghost get struck by lightning and can't remember each other.

added.title: Chili Cook-Off
added.description: Benson wants to get some street cred with the Park Managers' Association and win the big chili cook-off.

added.title: Daddy Issues
added.description: C.J. wants to win a "cut the Cheeser's" card at a mini-golf tournament.

added.title: El Anuncio
added.description: Los Watterson se ven obligados a alquilar su casa a un par de cabras ancianas que se desmayan.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Posesion
added.description: Richard Watterson parece estar sobrenaturalmente unido a su viejo refrigerador.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Amo
added.description: Los Watterson juegan un juego de rol fantástico para resolver sus diferencias.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Tu mama y la mia
added.description: Steven lleva a Garnet a conocer a algunos de sus nuevos amigos.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: El primo Jon
added.description: Cuando los Osos asisten a una reunión con la familia de Chloe, se convierten en víctimas de Jon, el travieso primo de Chloe.

added.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
added.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: Esto llega hasta el Once
added.description: Durante una última parada en una juguetería antes del viaje inaugural de Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max a través del Atlántico, Ben se encuentra con su antiguo bravucón, Kevin 11, que ahora tiene nuevos poderes. Es capaz de transformarse en alienígenas al igual que Ben, como el doble "pirata" de Cannonbolt: iWreckingbolt!

added.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
added.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

added.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
added.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

added.title: Polos Opuestos
added.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

added.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
added.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

added.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
added.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: El Arbol Perfecto
added.description: Chloe y Polar conducen hacia el norte para encontrar el árbol de Navidad perfecto. Mientras tanto, Pardo y Panda quedan a cargo de la decoración de la casa de Chloe.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik/Their Fights
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins./Their Fights: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

added.title: Haavik's Final Show/Miracle Planet
added.description: Haavik's Final Show: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!/ Miracle Planet: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

added.title: Problemas Dentales
added.description: A Puppycorn se le cae su primer diente, y Unikitty está emocionada por su hermanito, ique ahora recibirá la visita de la legendaria Hada de los Dientes! Pero cuando el Hada de los Dientes no aparece, Unikitty y sus amigos asumen la responsabilidad. ¿Acaso se meterán demasiado rápido y con demasiada soltura con los dientes sueltos y tocarán un nervio sensible?

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Jay Estrella del Rock
added.description: Dentro de Primer Imperio, los ninjas se encuentran en un territorio desconocido e intentan encontrar a Jay y escapar de los Visores Rojos de Unagami.

added.title: Isla Dyer
added.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Nivel Trece
added.description: Cyrus Borg descubre un secreto sobre Primer Imperio y  los ninjas enfrentan al Mecánico que escapó e intenta alcanzar el Nivel 13 para entrar al juego.

added.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
added.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

added.title: Yo Soy Okino
added.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

added.title: Juego tenebroso
added.description: Últimamente, la noche semanal de juegos de mesa de la banda se volvió demasiado competitiva, así que cuando Unikitty encuentra un viejo y espeluznante juego de mesa que claramente está embrujado, los deseos de ganar del grupo quedan dados vuelta, pero con o sin embrujo, iquieren ser los primeros en cruzar la línea de llegada!

added.title: El Libro Final
added.description: El último libro de fantasía de la serie favorita de Kelsey desaparece de la biblioteca. Por eso, Craig decide ayudarla a resolver el misterio de quién se lo llevó.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe pasa tiempo con los Osos con el objetivo de investigarlos para una presentación que tiene que hacer pronto. Pero cuando los Osos le dan un vistazo a su informe aburrido, deciden ponerle un poco de emoción con datos exagerados sobre sí mismos y su estilo de vida.

added.title: Nos Equivocamos
added.description: iK.O., Rad y Enid rompen por accidente una de las preciadas posesiones del Sr. Gar!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: The Dynamo Dynamic
added.description: Axel finds himself at the center of a disagreement between Sarge and Masko over what's more important in battle - the weapon or the one who wields it - after Dynamo bonds the trio together!

added.title: We Messed Up
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid accidentally break one of Mr. Gar's prized possessions!

added.title: Demasiados Tesoros
added.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Access Denied
added.description: When Axel and the team try to figure out what Sarge Charge's secret weapon is, they get ejected from the house by his newly upgraded security system and must fight their way back inside before Madcap does.

added.title: Fuego y Hielo
added.description: Cuando Master Frown le provoca a Unikitty un ataque de ira que se vuelve demasiado destructivo, ella desea que su faceta de Rage Kitty ya no sea parte de ella. Gracias a un nuevo invento de la Dra. Fox, el E-MoteTV, la princesa consigue su deseo: iRage Kitty y Nice Unikitty se dividen en dos! Pero ahora que Unikitty es incapaz de enfadarse, aprende que reprimir la ira nunca es algo bueno.

added.title: Swing Set Jet Set
added.description: Axel and the team battle Princess SugarSalt for possession of Bearbarian's hammer, traded to her by one of their own - Galileo!

added.title: Amigo roca
added.description: Unikitty descubre que el único otro amigo de Puppycorn es una roca vieja y aburrida. Incentivado a ""hacer más amigos"", Puppycorn no puede encontrar a alguien con quien sienta afinidad, hasta que sigue el consejo de Unikitty y decide literalmente hacer un nuevo amigo con las mejores partes de sus amigos. Esto no irá bien.

added.title: Side Kicked
added.description: Zoe builds her own battle suit in hopes of joining Axel's team. The only problem? She can't shrink! Hijinks ensue as a full-sized Zoe tries to assist Axel & co. in a battle against Pyrant and his army of mind-control drones.

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Escape de la Cena Familiar
added.description: En el arroyo se disputa una enorme pelea con globos acuáticos, pero Craig está atrapado en la cena familiar, a menos que pueda escapar.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Caos en la cocina
added.description: Después de lesionarse en su lugar de trabajo, Richard no puede hacer sus tareas de criado. Unikitty y los demás se encargan de una simple tarea: limpiar la cocina. Esta actividad increíblemente aburrida es un desafío para nuestros héroes, que buscan todas las formas posibles de no hacerla. ¿Serán capaces de alcanzar esta meta y traer de regreso a Richard?

added.title: Porcupunk Rock
added.description: Madcap turns to Axel and his team for help after a sonic upgrade to Porcupunk threatens to bring down the house.

added.title: Monstruo en el Jardin
added.description: Craig está decidido a atrapar al monstruo que ha estado desatando un caos en el jardín del abuelo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Tripping the Light Fantastic
added.description: Mega Man tries to save Dr. Light from a date with "Mari," who's actually Hypno Woman in disguise!

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Mi Papa Puede Vencer a Tu Papa
added.description: Cuando un bravucón dice que su papá puede darle una paliza a la mamá de K.O., nuestro héroe acepta con alegría el desafío en nombre de Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Running Wild
added.description: Student elections get blown out of proportion (literally) when Air Man lends his support to Aki's rival for class president, Peter Punk.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: Unfriendly Competition
added.description: Aki must set aside a petty rivalry with Bert Wily in order to stop Chemistry Man from wreaking havoc at Silicon Central's Field Day.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Fire Man and Wave Man team up to evaporate the city's water supply, forcing Mega Man to team up with an ally of his own- Suna.

added.title: I.C.E. (In Case of Emergency)
added.description: When Ice Man decides to be a hero, Mega Man, influenced by Ice Man's literalness, steps down from the hero biz until a true crisis snaps him out of it.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
added.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Conoce a Tu Mama
added.description: K.O. quiere sorprender a Carol con un regalo para el Día de la Madre, pero no sabe qué comprarle.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Know Your Mom
added.description: KO wants to surprise Carol with a gift for Mother's Day, but doesn't know what to get her.

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Nuestros héroes juegan un juego de un tragamonedas que los hace enfrentarse a sus temores más grandes.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Our heroes play an arcade game that makes them face their greatest fears.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Showdown Part I
added.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: All Aboard the Space Train
added.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Hide and Seek
added.description: A game of hide and seek uncovers a neglected remnant from Uncle Grandpa's past.

added.title: Booster's Gold
added.description: Green Arrow becomes involved with Booster Gold when he discovers that the self-centered superhero has brought dinosaurs back from the past for a money-making venture.

added.title: Boo-ray for Bizarro
added.description: When the diabolical Amazo attacks the League and begins to steal their powers one-by-one, the klutzy, backwards-thinking Bizarro becomes our heroes' last hope to turn things around.

added.title: The Cave of Gelatinous Doom!
added.description: The Warriors don't have a worthy adventure to use their impressive new skull-and-crossbones-emblazoned Bonehead Magisword until they are sent on a quest to battle a mighty slime beast in the Dungeon of Gelatinous Doom!

added.title: Best Day Ever
added.description: Joker frees Luthor with a mother box and forces him to spend the day together, hopping all over the world, with the Justice League hot on their trail trying to catch up.

added.title: Dias de gloria
added.description: K.O. escribe un informe escolar sobre Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Glory Days
added.description: KO does a school report on Carol.

added.title: Squideo Games
added.description: When Vambre and Prohyas are hired for separate gigs, they end up having to battle each other to claim a rare Squideo from Lake Sprite in Galacton.

added.title: Grounded
added.description: Uncle Grandpa must fix his mistake after he helps a grounded teen go to a party.

added.title: Don't Read the Comments
added.description: An obsession with comments and criticisms about him on the Board of Opinions drives Prohyas nuts, affecting Warrior missions for the worse and raising Vambre's ire, I mean, concerns.

added.title: Transylbabies
added.description: A mission to babysit Snowmanpire babies in Transylbiria leads Vambre and Prohyas to attack the local monster townsfolk in misguided attempts to keep the Snowbabies safe.

added.title: Continue?
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman hires the Warriors to retrieve the Orb of Sphericity from a temple in Galacton. The odd thing is, this temple has save points! When the Warriors are defeated, they respawn, but Vambre remembers what happened and Prohyas does not.

added.title: Dog Day
added.description: When a father refuses his daughter's request for a dog, Uncle Grandpa vows to teach the girl responsibility by becoming a dog.

added.title: Big Trouble for Tiny Miracle
added.description: Tiny Miracle allows the gang to take advantage of his generosity at the expense of his own health.

added.title: La Broma
added.description: Cuando intenta demostrarles a los Thundercachorros que no es un adulto aburrido (como Tigro), León-O ignora sus instintos y se mete con un cristal claramente malvado.

added.title: Cambiando Objetos
added.description: Axel y el equipo luchan contra la Princesa SugarSalt por la posesión del martillo de Bearbarian, que le vendió uno de los suyos: iGalileo!

added.title: La Leyenda de Boggy Ben
added.description: León-O se apoderó del último frasco de Thundersnaps, ilas mejores galletas disponibles en Thundera! Pero un frasco de galletas difícil de abrir hace que León-O y Chitara terminen yendo tras la leyenda de Boggy Ben.

added.title: Sin Atajos
added.description: Tras esforzarse por mantener el ritmo en las batallas, Adorabat consigue una armadura cibernética. ¿Pero podrán unos nuevos y sofisticados poderes compensar la falta de experiencia?

added.title: Ataque de Thermometron 9000
added.description: Axel debe lidiar con Galileo y Bobbie para apagar un termostato deshonesto, que Slobot actualizó incorrectamente, ya que sumerge la casa en zonas extremadamente frías y calientes.

added.title: Taladro
added.description: Pantro se está hartando de tener que arreglar cosas constantemente por todo el Cubil Felino, lo cual es una pena porque los Thundercats están a punto de ser atacados por un robot perforador imparable...ique va a romper todo!

added.title: Acceso Denegado
added.description: Cuando Axel y el equipo intentan descubrir cuál es el arma secreta de Sarge Charge, son expulsados ​​de la casa por su sistema de seguridad recientemente actualizado y deben abrirse camino antes de que Madcap lo haga.

added.title: Juntos por Siempre
added.description: Connie tiene una visión muy clara de su futuro, y Steven quiere asegurarse de ser parte de esa visión.

added.title: Drawn to Ancestry
added.description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Asian-American Pacific Islander Heritage Month and recognizing amazing kids who learn from their elders to pave their future! We're honoring the special bond between kids and their grandparents as they are Drawn To Ancestry.

added.title: Exodo Parte 1
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: Companera Nueva
added.description: Zoe construye su propio traje de batalla con la esperanza de unirse al equipo de Axel. ¿El único problema? Ella no puede encogerse! Se producen hijinks cuando una Zoe de tamaño completo intenta ayudar a Axel & co. en una batalla contra Pyrant y su ejército de drones de control mental.

added.title: Bismuto Casual
added.description: Perla invita a Bismuto a la pista de patinaje para darle una lección sobre cómo forjar relaciones humanas.

added.title: La Dinamica del Dinamo
added.description: iAxel se encuentra en el centro de un desacuerdo entre Sarge y Masko sobre lo que es más importante en la batalla, el arma o el que lo maneja, después de que Dynamo une al trío!

added.title: Exodo Parte 2
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Fallen Arches/The Mane Event
added.description: Fallen Arches: When a gang of old-time villains come out of retirement, the girls enlist the best superhero team of the past to save the city./The Mane Event: Bubbles and Buttercup are playing with Blossom's beautiful locks when an accident happens. Now, Blossom is too embarrassed to put up a good fight.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Sigue la corriente
added.description: Cuando Sal se queda en lo de Vic y Val, los chicos no lo soportan como compañero, pero finalmente descubren lo genial y mágico que es.

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Let's Take a Moment
added.description: Mr. Gar and Carol fight a villain from their past.

added.title: CarolQuest
added.description: Carol is forced to bring KO along as she defends the Plaza from a new threat.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Hurricane Dilliss
added.description: Things in the Wendle household are turned upside down when Mary's mom Dyllis comes to visit, butting her way into every corner of Clarence, Mary and Chad's life.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Clarence Wendle and the Eye of Coogan
added.description: Clarence and other students find the crusty old journal of Coogan filled with clues leading to a mysterious treasure. Clarence spearheads the team of treasure hunters to journey through the perils of Aberdale seeking the lost Eye of Coogan.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: Memory Lane of Pain
added.description: While going through the Professor's scrapbook, Bubbles starts to question if she's ever been a hero.

added.title: Imagine That
added.description: The Girls have to battle Him after he causes Bubbles' imagination to run wild.

added.title: Phantasm Chasm
added.description: After getting sucked into Jared's favorite board game, Buttercup is forced to team-up with him in order to save her sisters.

added.title: Tooth or Consequences
added.description: Blossom's fear of the dentist's drill causes her to avoid it at all costs.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend Bliss, her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Never Been Blissed
added.description: With a parasitic alien on the loose in their school, the Powerpuff Girls and Bliss have to find a way to stop it before the big dance.

added.title: The Buttercup Job
added.description: Buttercup joins Jemmica in a quest for adventure, but how far will she go?

added.title: Power of Four
added.description: When a long-forgotten figure from the Professor's past returns, the Powerpuff Girls' life as superheroes is turned upside down. With some of their greatest foes choosing this time to strike, the Powerpuff Girls will have to band together like never before to stop them.

added.title: Get That BORFL!
added.description: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven, with the Warriors resorting to Magiswords to thwart the critter.

added.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
added.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

added.title: Bad Heir Day
added.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

added.title: School's In, Oh Bummer
added.description: It turns out that Vambre and Prohyas didn't graduate the Adventure Academy after all and need to go back to school earn their diplomas!

added.title: Quest for Knowledge
added.description: After a flashback where we learn the origins of the Warriors passion for Magiswords, they return to Adventure Academy where Professor Cyrus sets V and P and their former classmates on a quest to find the Legendary Knowledge Magisword.

added.title: My Mom
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are forced to work under Muscle Man and endure his repetitive jokes.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Caveman
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

added.title: Cool Cubed
added.description: The guys need to unfreeze Thomas' brain after he chugs a slushy.

added.title: Butt Dial
added.description: Mordecai pocket dials an embarrassing message on Margaret's phone.

added.title: Big Winner
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby give Muscle Man a lottery ticket for his birthday.

added.title: Busted Cart
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby bust up the cart while doing stunts and have to figure out a way to fix it.

added.title: Dead at Eight
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to babysit Death's kid.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 1
added.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

added.title: A Jolt from the Past
added.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

added.title: Have I Got a Deal for You
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop a giant rampaging alien from destroying Bellwood while dealing with a peace-loving alien-rights activist who doesn't want it hurt. (Introducing Hokestar, Solid Plugg 1st appearance, Pax, Sunder.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Outbreak
added.description: When Dr. Psychobos steals a part out of the Omnitrix, causing chaotic side effects, it's up to Ben, Rook, and a small team of Plumbers get everything back to normal. (Introducing new Ben alien Kickin' Hawk, temp Ben alien Walkatrout, Upchuck Rook.)

added.title: Gone Fishin'
added.description: When their fishing trip in Undertown takes a bizarre twist, Ben, Rook, and Grandpa Max, begin their search for a ship-bottling alien pirate who has captured Magister Patelliday. (Introducing Capt. Cork.)

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Captain Bamboozle
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk decides to create some mischief by endowing Shazam's well-meaning Uncle Dudley with superpowers bigger than anyone in the league.

added.title: Idolo De La Liga De La Justicia: Edicion Del Segundo Mejor Equipo
added.description: La Liga de la Justicia organiza un concurso de talentos para encontrar al segundo mejor equipo de superhéroes.

added.title: Idolo De La Liga De La Justicia P2- Edicion Del Segundo Mejor Equipo
added.description: La competición se intensifica y los Titanes deben encontrar una forma de vencer a la Colmena.

added.title: Los Jovenes Titanes vrum: primera parte
added.description: En este episodio de "Fuerza Turbo Titanes", los Titanes obtienen la habilidad de convertirse en autos.

added.title: Los Jovenes Titanes vrum: segunda parte
added.description: En la emocionante conclusión de "Fuerza Turbo Titanes", los Titanes deben aprender a trabajar juntos para detener al Doctor Militar.

added.title: El Benefactor
added.description: Los Osos ayudan a Chloe a presentar su proyecto de ciencias para un concurso escolar. Pero el rival de Chloe complica las cosas.

added.title: La Noche Brilla Especial: Capitulo 1
added.description: Cyborg queda atrapado en una realidad alternativa con un Dragón que quiere robarse una canción para sus propios fines malvados.

added.title: La Noche Brilla Especial: Capitulo 2
added.description: Sin Cyborg, Chico Bestia se siente perdido y decide encontrarse a sí mismo, pero termina conociendo a una leyenda de la música.

added.title: La Noche Brilla Especial: Capitulo 3
added.description: Los Titanes regresan a la realidad alternativa para salvar a Cyborg, pero serán capaces de derrotar al Dragón?

added.title: La Noche Brilla Especial: Capitulo 4
added.description: En una batalla final épica, los Titanes y sus amigos músicos se ponen en guardia contra el Dragón para controlar La Noche Brillará.

added.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 1
added.description: La Liga de la Justicia organiza un concurso de talentos para encontrar a un superhéroe digno de unirse al equipo.

added.title: Proximo Idolo de la Liga de la Justicia: Parte 2
added.description: La competencia se enciende cuando Robin hace lo imposible por ganar.

added.title: Profesor Lampwick
added.description: El profesor de Chloe es demasiado malvado como para concederle una reunión para discutir sus calificaciones bajas. Los Osos toman el asunto en sus propias manos para ayudar, lo cual le trae más problemas a Chloe.

added.title: Atrapagritos
added.description: Cuando una caries obliga a Ben a ir al dentista, su día empeora aún más cuando el malévolo mago Hex usa un atrapasueños para materializar los miedos de nuestro héroe y los transporta con él a un lugar pesadillesco.

added.title: Mi Bella Carol
added.description: K.O., Enid y Rad se unen para ayudar a Carol para una ocasión especial.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Presentando a La Creatura
added.description: Cuando Max se queda dormido antes de una doble función, Ben y Gwen se ven obligados a salvar el autocine solos. Ocurre que el malvado mago Hex da vida al monstruo de una película, que aterroriza a los espectadores.

added.title: Animorfosis
added.description: El trío Tennyson excava fósiles de dinosaurio, pero Ben no sabe que Vilgax y el Dr. Animal se complotaron para robar ADN alien del Omnitrix, pero, una vez extraído el ADN, Vilgax traiciona a su cómplice. Ahora Ben debe aliarse con el malvado doctor si quiere tener la oportunidad de derrotar al gran villano. Pero ¿puede confiar en el Dr. Animal?

added.title: Deseo de Verano
